This is according to the 2019 Global Hunger Index, which calculates the nutrition situation in 117 countries. 

This year the Central African Republic tops the index, and 43 out of the 117 countries ranked have serious hunger levels. The report was released as yesterday marked World Food day. Simone Pott is spokesperson for the aid organisation, Welthungerhilfe, one of the agencies that wrote the report… --ChannelAfrica--